# GitHub Project Tracker

This project is a small automation tool that scans a GitHub repository to detect new completed projects. (WIP)

The script connects to the GitHub API and inspects specific folders in the repository that contain portfolio projects. It identifies project directories, reads their README files, and determines whether a project is complete or still marked as a work in progress.

The goal of this tool is to automate part of the portfolio workflow by detecting when a project has been completed and preparing information that can later be used to automatically generate LinkedIn posts summarizing the work.

This project is currently focused on:

* connecting to the GitHub API using PyGithub
* scanning repository folders for project directories
* identifying project README files
* building logic to detect completed projects

Future development will include generating AI-written summaries and automatically creating LinkedIn draft posts for newly completed projects.
